+```
+
+### Data flow: input вҶ’ state update вҶ’ render
+
+```text
+1. raw event (keydown / pointerdown+up)
+        в”Ӯ
+2. InputPipeline.normalize(event)  в”Җв”Җв–¶  Intent
+        в”Ӯ   Intent = { type: 'move'|'undo'|'reset', dir?: 'N'|'S'|'E'|'W' }
+        в”Ӯ   - keymap (WASDвҶ”arrows, U=undo, R=reset)
+        в”Ӯ   - swipe: distance threshold + dominant axis  в”Җв”Җв–¶  move dir
+        в”Ӯ   - pointer/touch on buttons  в”Җв”Җв–¶  button intent
+        в–ј
+3. GameShell.dispatch(intent)
+        в”Ӯ   - if Animator.isBusy() and intent is a move:
+        в”Ӯ       snap current tween to end, commit, then start new move
+        в”Ӯ       (animation interruption вҖ” see Key Decisions)
+        в”Ӯ   - else: compute next state immediately
+        в–ј
+4. gameReducer(state, intent)  в”Җв”Җв–¶  { state: newState, anim?: AnimSpec }
+        в”Ӯ   - move: validate target tile; if push, validate beyond-box tile
+        в”Ӯ   - push pushes box; both player+box move 1 tile
+        в”Ӯ   - undo: pop last entry from history stack
+        в”Ӯ   - reset: clone initialState
+        в”Ӯ   - winCheck after every move/push
+        в”Ӯ   - returns AnimSpec { from, to, duration, entities:[player,box?] }
+        в–ј
+5. Animator.start(AnimSpec)   // 100вҖ“150ms linear tween over world-coords
+        в”Ӯ   GameShell.state = newState (logical/integer positions update now)
+        в”Ӯ   Animator holds the visual-from/to used only for rendering
+        в–ј
+6. rAF loop (every frame)
+        в”Ӯ   t = Animator.elapsed()
+        в”Ӯ   visualPos = lerp(from, to, t/duration)   // linear
+        в–ј
+7. Renderer.draw(state, visualPos)
+        в”Ӯ   - clear canvas
+        в”Ӯ   - draw grid: floor/walls/targets from level static data
+        в”Ӯ   - draw boxes (green if on target)
+        в”Ӯ   - draw player at visualPos
+        в”Ӯ   - draw HUD overlay (move count, level name) via DOM, not canvas
+        в–ј
+8. Canvas pixels painted
+```
+
+## Alternatives Evaluated
+
+| Approach | Strengths | Weaknesses | Verdict |
+|----------|-----------|-----------|---------|
+| **A. Functional reducer + thin shell (RECOMMENDED)** | Pure reducer is trivially unit-testable (input вҶ’ expected state, no canvas/DOM); state is immutable so undo = replay or snapshot stack; clear separation of simulation vs presentation; no framework dependency; matches Vitest's natural unit shape. | Reducer must return both logical state AND an anim spec, slightly more ceremony; animator lives outside the pure core, so test setup needs a tiny fake clock. | **Adopt.** Best testability-to-complexity ratio for a 10-level game. |
+| **B. Single Game class (god-object)** | One place to look; simplest mental model initially; this is the classic hand-rolled canvas game pattern. | Mixes pure logic with rAF, canvas, localStorage, input вҶ’ untestable without a full DOM/canvas harness; grows into a 600-line class; undo/win-check logic entangled with rendering; violates "no god-objects" acceptance criterion. | **Reject.** Fails the module-boundary acceptance criterion and makes Vitest units painful. |
+| **C. ECS-lite (entities / components / systems)** | Industry-standard game pattern; scales to many entity types; cache-friendly data layout. | Massive overkill for a game with exactly two dynamic entity types (player + boxes); component stores add indirection with no payoff; harder to reason about the Sokoban invariant (boxes push as a unit with player); more boilerplate than the reducer. | **Reject.** Premature abstraction for 10 levels / вүӨ~30 entities. Revisit only if scope grows to entities with independent behaviors. |
+| **D. Solid/React + canvas view** | Familiar UI dev model; reactive state for HUD/level-picker. | Adds a runtime + bundle weight for a canvas game where the canvas itself is imperative; HUD reactivity can be done with a 20-line emitter; framework lifecycle fights the rAF loop; violates simplicity-first. | **Reject for core.** Optional: use a tiny signal for the *HUD/level-picker only* if DOM updates become tedious вҖ” but plain event emitter suffices. |
+
+> Confidence: **HIGH** on rejecting B and C; **HIGH** on D for the core loop; **MEDIUM** on whether a tiny signal lib is worth it for the HUD (depends on picker UI complexity, see stack.md).
+
+## Key Decisions
+
+### Project layout (file-tree sketch)
+
+```text
+sokoban/
+в”ңв”Җв”Җ index.html                  # <canvas#game> + HUD DOM skeleton
+в”ңв”Җв”Җ levels/
+в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ level-01.json ... level-10.json
+в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ schema.json             # JSON Schema for a level (documented)
+в”ңв”Җв”Җ src/
+в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ main.ts                 # bootstrap: wire shell to canvas + HUD
+в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.ts                # Tile, Direction, GameState, Intent, AnimSpec, Level
+в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ core/
+в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ reducer.ts          # pure: (state, intent) -> { state, anim? }
+в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ winCheck.ts         # pure: all boxes-on-targets?
