+
+### Module boundaries (no god-objects)
+
+- **`core/`** вҖ” pure functions only. No imports from `render/`, `input/`, `anim/`, `dom`. Importable in Vitest with zero DOM setup. This is the *simulation*. Every acceptance-critical rule (move validity, push, win, undo) lives here.
+- **`shell/gameShell.ts`** вҖ” the only module that knows about all subsystems. It is intentionally thin: it forwards intents to the reducer, feeds anim specs to the animator, and asks the renderer to draw each frame. It owns the rAF loop but contains no game rules.
+- **`render/`** вҖ” receives `(state, visualPos, ctx)` and paints. No mutation of state, no input handling. Re-draws the whole canvas each frame (10Г—10-ish grid вҶ’ trivially cheap; partial redraws are premature optimization вҖ” **HIGH** confidence this is fine for вүӨ~30 tilesГ—entities).
+- **`input/`** вҖ” produces `Intent` values only; never touches state directly.
+- **`storage/`** вҖ” single owner of `localStorage`; everything else goes through it so the key namespace and serialization stay centralized.
+- **`ui/`** вҖ” DOM overlays (level picker, HUD, win banner, mobile buttons). Kept out of canvas so responsive layout (NFR-4) is handled by CSS, not canvas math.
+
+### State model (immutable GameState)
+
+```text
+type GameState = {
+  levelId: string;
+  static: { width: number; height: number; walls: Set<Coord>; targets: Set<Coord> };
+  player: Coord;                 // integer tile coords (logical)
+  boxes: Coord[];                // order-stable; index = box identity
+  moveCount: number;
+  history: HistoryEntry[];       // undo stack, see below
+  won: boolean;
+};
+```
+
+- `static` is derived once from the `Level` and never copied per move (shared reference; reducer must not mutate it).
+- Each reducer call returns a *new* `GameState` object with shallow-copied `boxes`/`history` arrays; `static` is reused by reference. Cheap for вүӨ30 boxes.
+- `won` is a derived flag recomputed by `winCheck` inside the reducer rather than computed in the renderer (single source of truth).
+
+### Undo stack representation
+
+```text
+type HistoryEntry = {
+  player: Coord;          // player position BEFORE the move
+  pushedBoxIndex?: number;// index into boxes[] if a box was pushed
+  boxFrom?: Coord;        // box position BEFORE the push
+  moveCount: number;      // before the move (== state.moveCount - 1 after)
+};
+```
+
+- One entry per successful move (push or walk). Walks store only `player`+`moveCount`; pushes add `pushedBoxIndex`+`boxFrom`.
+- **Undo** = pop entry вҶ’ restore `player`, restore `box[pushedBoxIndex]` to `boxFrom`, decrement `moveCount`, set `won = winCheck(state)`. No animation spec is needed for undo in v1 (snap); if desired, undo can animate by emitting an `AnimSpec` with reversed from/to. **MEDIUM** confidence on animating undo вҖ” snap is simpler and matches "no queue blocking" NFR-5.
+- **Unlimited depth** (NFR-6): the array grows unbounded; for 10 levels this is bounded by the level's solvable move count in practice (вүӨ low thousands), so no cap and no ring buffer. **HIGH** confidence.
+- Alternative considered: full-state snapshots per move. Rejected вҖ” entry-based undo is O(1) memory per move vs O(level-size) snapshots, and entry-based exposes push semantics directly for tests.
+
+### Win-check algorithm
+
+```text
+winCheck(state): boolean =
+  state.boxes.length === state.static.targets.size
+  && state.boxes.every(b => state.static.targets.has(b))
+```
+
+- O(boxes) per check, called once per move inside the reducer.
+- Cheap and exact. No incremental tracking needed (a Set-difference "boxes not on target" counter would add state for no gain at this scale).
+- Must be re-run after **undo** and **reset** too (a pushed-then-undone box can re-trigger or clear `won`).
+- Edge: a level is only valid if `boxes.length === targets.size` вҖ” enforced by `level/validate.ts` at load time. **HIGH** confidence.
+
+### Render loop
+
+- Single `requestAnimationFrame` loop in `gameShell.ts`, started on level load, cancelled on level exit.
+- Each frame: compute `visualPos` from the animator (if busy) or use logical coords (if idle), then `renderer.draw(...)`.
+- **Fixed timestep is NOT needed**: Sokoban has no continuous physics; the only time-dependent thing is the 100вҖ“150ms tween, and a wall-clock-based linear lerp is frame-rate independent by construction (`t = now - startTs`). The logical simulation only advances on discrete input. **HIGH** confidence rAF-with-wall-clock beats fixed-timestep here (fixed timestep solves a problem this game does not have).
+- Redraw the entire canvas every frame. At вүӨ~30 entities on a вүӨ~15Г—15 grid, fillRect cost is negligible and avoids dirty-rect bookkeeping. **HIGH** confidence.
+
+### Input pipeline
+
+```text
+event вҶ’ InputPipeline вҶ’ Intent вҶ’ GameShell.dispatch вҶ’ reducer
+```
+
+- Keyboard: `keydown` вҶ’ map to `move(dir)` / `undo` / `reset`. Prevent default for game keys to stop page scroll. Ignore auto-repeat (`e.repeat`) вҖ” one move per physical press (matches "one tile per keypress" FR-1). **HIGH**.
+- Touch: `pointerdown` records start; `pointerup` computes delta. If `|delta| > SWIPE_MIN` (вүҲ24px) and one axis dominates вҶ’ `move(dir)`. Taps on buttons handled by the buttons themselves. Pointer Events (not separate touch+mouse) covers both. **HIGH**.
+- Buttons (DOM, in `ui/`): undo/reset/level-picker вҶ’ emit the same `Intent` shape through the same `dispatch` path, so touch-button and keyboard share logic.
+
+### Animation interruption (NFR-5)
+
+Two viable strategies; the second is recommended.
+
+1. **Queue inputs** вҖ” buffer intents until the tween finishes. Rejected: violates "no queue blocking" and feels laggy on rapid keypresses.
+2. **Snap-then-start (RECOMMENDED)** вҖ” when a new `move` intent arrives mid-tween:
+   - finalize the in-flight tween instantly: commit `visualPos := to`, mark animator idle;
+   - then run the reducer + start the new tween from the now-current logical position.
+   - Result: input is never blocked; the visible sprite may "jump" to the tile boundary then continue. With a 100вҖ“150ms tween this jump is rarely perceptible because the next intent usually arrives near the end of the previous tween. **HIGH** confidence this satisfies NFR-5.
+   - Implementation: `animator.snap()` sets `t = duration` and calls its onComplete; `dispatch` checks `animator.isBusy()` before computing the next state.
+
+- `undo`/`reset` mid-animation: snap the current tween first (same path), then apply. **HIGH**.
+
+### Level loading
+
+- Use `import.meta.glob('./../levels/level-*.json', { eager: true, as: 'json' })` in `level/loader.ts`. Vite inlines the JSON at build time вҶ’ no runtime `fetch`, works on GitHub Pages static hosting with no base-path issues, and is fully typed via `as: 'json'`.
+- Loader returns `Record<string, Level>` keyed by path; sort by numeric suffix вҶ’ `Level[]`.
+- `validate.ts` checks each: required fields, `boxes.length === targets.size`, player/boxes/targets inside grid bounds, no box or player on a wall. Invalid level вҶ’ throw with level id (caught in shell вҶ’ show error UI).
+- Alternative вҖ” runtime `fetch('./levels/level-XX.json')`: works in `dev` but breaks under GitHub Pages subpaths unless `base` is configured; adds an async init dance. Rejected for static-hosting simplicity. **HIGH** confidence eager-glob is correct; see stack.md for the parallel comparison.
+
+### Persistence layer
+
+- `storage/storage.ts` is the *only* module touching `localStorage`. Namespace all keys: `sokoban:v1:cleared` (array of level ids), `sokan:v1:best:<levelId>` (number). Versioned prefix enables future migration.
+- API: `getCleared()`, `markCleared(id, moves)`, `getBest(id)`, `clearAll()`.
+- Wrap `localStorage` access in try/catch (private mode / quota) вҶ’ degrade gracefully to in-memory defaults. Log once, never throw into the game loop.
+- Serialization: `JSON.stringify` for the cleared array; numbers are already strings. No need for idb-keyval/localforage at this data volume. **HIGH** (see stack.md).
+
+## Risks & Mitigations
+
+- **Risk: reducer returns both state and anim-spec, blurring purity.** *Mitigation:* keep `AnimSpec` a plain data value derived *from* the transition (from/to are just the old/new coords). The reducer has no side effects; the spec is descriptive. Tests assert on the returned state and on `anim.from/to/duration` as data. **HIGH** confidence this stays pure.
+- **Risk: `Set<Coord>` mutation when sharing `state.static` across reducer outputs.** *Mitigation:* `static` is constructed once per level and treated as readonly; `core/` never calls mutating Set methods on it. Add a `readonly`-style JSDoc and a unit test that runs N moves and asserts `static` referential equality. **HIGH**.
+- **Risk: animation interruption causes visual jitter on rapid keypresses.** *Mitigation:* snap-then-start keeps logical state consistent; if jitter is observed, lower tween duration toward 100ms (the NFR floor) so snaps land closer to the natural end. Tunable constant in `animator.ts`. **MEDIUM**.
+- **Risk: responsive layout breaks tile-grid alignment (NFR-4).** *Mitigation:* size the canvas from `window` dimensions in `main.ts`, compute `tileSize = min(w/cols, h/rows)`, recompute on `resize`. HUD/picker are DOM/CSS, not canvas, so they reflow independently. **HIGH** confidence this decouples the two layout concerns.
+- **Risk: GitHub Pages base path breaks asset/level URLs.** *Mitigation:* eager-glob inlines levels into the JS bundle (no asset URL at runtime). For any future runtime assets, set Vite `base: './'` or use `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`. **HIGH**.
+- **Risk: undo-then-win state drift (win flag stale after undo).** *Mitigation:* reducer always recomputes `won` via `winCheck` on undo and reset, not only on move. Covered by a Vitest case: win вҶ’ undo вҶ’ assert `won === false`. **HIGH**.
+- **Risk: pointer/swipe accidentally fires on button taps.** *Mitigation:* buttons call `e.stopPropagation()` so the swipe handler on the canvas area never sees them; also the swipe handler ignores events whose target is inside `ui/` overlays. **MEDIUM**.
+- **Risk: localStorage disabled (private mode).** *Mitigation:* storage layer catches and falls back to in-memory; game remains fully playable, just non-persistent. **HIGH**.
+
+## Confidence Summary
+
+| Finding | Confidence |
+|---|---|
+| Functional reducer + thin shell is the right core pattern | **HIGH** |
+| Single Game class rejected (god-object) | **HIGH** |
+| ECS-lite rejected (over-abstraction) | **HIGH** |
+| React/Solid rejected for the core loop | **HIGH** |
+| Full-canvas redraw per frame is fine at this scale | **HIGH** |
+| rAF + wall-clock tween (no fixed timestep) | **HIGH** |
+| Entry-based undo stack (vs full snapshots) | **HIGH** |
+| Eager `import.meta.glob` level loading | **HIGH** |
+| localStorage-only persistence (no idb/localforage) | **HIGH** |
+| Snap-then-start animation interruption satisfies NFR-5 | **MEDIUM** |
+| Undo as snap (not animated) in v1 | **MEDIUM** |
+| Tiny signal lib worth it for HUD/picker only | **MEDIUM** (see stack.md) |
