+
+## Summary of Highest-Priority Risks (BLOCKER severity)
+
+1. **#3 Undo correctness** вҖ” snapshot player AND boxes; test push/walk/reset-undo.
+2. **#4 Undo mid-animation** вҖ” logical state commits at input; tween is render-only.
+3. **#5 Animation interrupt** вҖ” snap-then-restart tween; never queue inputs.
+4. **#6 localStorage throws (private mode/quota)** вҖ” wrap all access in try/catch; degrade gracefully.
+5. **#9 Touch swipe scrolls the page** вҖ” `touch-action: none` + scoped Pointer Events + `preventDefault`.
+6. **#11 GitHub Pages base path** вҖ” env-driven `base`; verify with E2E against built artifact.
+7. **#12 JSON level path under sub-path deploy** вҖ” use `import.meta.glob` eager, or `BASE_URL`-prefixed fetch.
+
+All BLOCKERs have concrete, low-complexity mitigations and should be addressed in the architecture/plan phases before any feature code is written.
