+## Final Selection
+
+| Component | Choice | Version | Purpose | Confidence |
+|-----------|--------|---------|---------|------------|
+| Language | TypeScript | ^5.6 (project-pinned) | All source; no JS-only files | HIGH |
+| Build tool | Vite | ^8.1.2 (latest) | Dev server, build, `import.meta.glob`, `vite preview` for E2E | HIGH |
+| Package manager | npm | (bundled with Node 20+) | Lockfile `package-lock.json` | HIGH |
+| Level loading | `import.meta.glob('./levels/*.json', { eager: true, query: '?json', import: 'default' })` | Vite native | Inline all 10 level JSONs at build time; no fetch, no base-path bugs | HIGH |
+| State management | Plain TS `GameModel` class + ~20-line `subscribe()` emitter | 0 deps | Hold grid/player/boxes/undo/move-count; notify render loop + DOM labels | HIGH |
+| Rendering | HTML5 Canvas 2D (`getContext('2d')`, `fillRect`) | native | Flat-vector tiles per NFR-3 color scheme | HIGH |
+| Animation | Vanilla `requestAnimationFrame` linear tween helper (~30 lines) | 0 deps | 100вҖ“150ms linear, parallel, interruptible (NFR-5) | HIGH |
+| Game loop | Single rAF loop, immediate sim on input, idle-stop when no tween | 0 deps | Frame-rate-independent via `performance.now()`; battery-friendly | HIGH |
+| Touch input | Native Pointer Events swipe helper (~25 lines) + `touch-action: none` | 0 deps | 4-direction swipe on mobile (NFR-4); unifies mouse/touch/pen | HIGH |
+| Keyboard input | `window.addEventListener('keydown', вҖҰ)` | 0 deps | Arrows/WASD/U/R (FR-1, FR-3, FR-4) | HIGH |
+| Persistence | Vanilla `localStorage` + `JSON.parse/stringify` in `storage.ts` | 0 deps | Cleared levels + best move counts (NFR-2); sync restore on load | HIGH |
+| Unit test runner | Vitest | ^4.1.9 | TS unit tests for move/push/win/undo/persistence/level-loading | HIGH |
+| Unit DOM env | happy-dom | ^20.10.6 | Lightweight DOM for the few DOM-touching tests (scoped via `environmentMatchGlobs`) | HIGH |
+| E2E test runner | @playwright/test | ^1.61.1 | Keyboard + touch E2E over the built static bundle | HIGH |
+| E2E server | `vite preview` of `dist/` (Playwright `webServer`) | Vite native | Tests the real static deploy artifact incl. `base` path | HIGH |
+| E2E projects | desktop (1280Г—720) + mobile (`devices['Pixel 7']`, `hasTouch:true`) | Playwright native | Covers NFR-4 touch + responsive layout | HIGH |
+| Deployment | GitHub Pages action uploading `dist/` | GitHub-provided | Static bundle from `vite build` | HIGH |
+| Commit convention | Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`вҖҰ) | n/a | Enforced in PR titles/commits | HIGH |
+| State-mgmt upgrade path (contingency) | `nanostores` | 1.4.0 | Only if reactive DOM surface grows beyond ~5 bound nodes | LOW (not adopted now) |
+| Animation upgrade path (contingency) | `motion` | 12.42.2 | Only if non-linear easing / keyframes are later required | LOW (not adopted now) |
+
+---
+
+## Risks & Mitigations
+
+- **Vite 8 + Node 20 minimum:** Vite 8 requires Node 20.19+ / 22.12+. The project pins
+  Node 20+; ensure CI and local use вүҘ 20.19 (use a `.nvmrc` with `20.19.0` or `22`). If
+  pinning to an older Node 20 patch is required, fall back to **Vite ^7.x** (also supported
+  by Vitest 4.1.9 per its peer range `^6.0.0 || ^7.0.0 || ^8.0.0`). **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Canvas 2D not implemented in happy-dom/jsdom:** Unit tests that exercise rendering must
+  mock `CanvasRenderingContext2D` methods (`fillRect`, `clearRect`, вҖҰ) with `vi.fn()`
+  spies. Pure game-logic tests (move/push/win/undo/storage/glob-load) need no canvas mock.
+  **Confidence: HIGH** on the requirement; **MEDIUM** on the exact mock surface (finalize
+  during implementation by listing the `ctx` methods actually called).
+- **GitHub Pages base path:** If the repo is not `<user>.github.io` root, `vite.config.ts`
+  must set `base: '/<repo>/'` (or `base: './'` for relative assets). The eager-glob choice
+  makes level loading immune to this (JSON is inlined), but any `fetch`/asset URL must
+  respect `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`. Recommendation A avoids this entirely. **Confidence:
+  HIGH.**
+- **Pointer Events on older iOS Safari:** Pointer Events are supported in Safari вүҘ 13
+  (2019). Set `touch-action: none` on the canvas to prevent page-scroll interference.
+  **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **`localStorage` in private mode:** Safari throws on `setItem` in private mode; the
+  `storage.ts` wrapper must `try/catch` both read and write and degrade gracefully
+  (in-memory only). **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Eager glob picks up stray JSON:** `import.meta.glob('./levels/*.json', вҖҰ)` will include
+  any `.json` added under `levels/`. Use a strict glob like `./levels/level-??.json` or
+  validate filenames in the parser to avoid accidentally shipping a `levels/test.json`.
+  **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Tween interruption correctness:** When a new move cancels an in-flight tween, the
+  "from" position of the new tween must be the **current interpolated** position, not the
+  last discrete tile вҖ” otherwise the sprite snaps. This is a one-line detail but easy to
+  get wrong; cover with a Vitest test. **Confidence: HIGH.**
+
+---
+
+## Out of Scope (intentionally not adopted)
+
+- **React / Solid / Vue** вҖ” Canvas 2D rendering is imperative; a UI framework would add
+  40вҖ“100 KB and a DOM-diffing model that does not match the render loop. Rejected.
+- **anime.js / motion** вҖ” solving a linear lerp with a 16вҖ“50 KB library violates
+  simplicity-first. Rejected (kept as LOW-confidence contingency only).
+- **Hammer.js** вҖ” unmaintained since 2016, superseded by Pointer Events. Rejected.
+- **idb-keyval / localforage** вҖ” IndexedDB wrappers for a < 1 KB sync-read persistence
+  need. Rejected.
+- **Fixed-timestep game loop** вҖ” designed for continuous physics, not discrete puzzle
+  moves with short linear tweens. Rejected.
+- **Zod / runtime schema validation for levels** вҖ” 10 hand-authored JSON files with a
+  documented schema; a hand-written `parseLevel(raw): Level | throws` validator is
+  sufficient and dependency-free. Rejected (note: if level count grows or levels become
+  community-supplied, revisit). **Confidence: MEDIUM.**
+
+---
+
+*Versions verified against the npm registry on 2026-07-01. Confidence labels reflect
+direct verification (HIGH), established-but-unverified-in-session patterns (MEDIUM), or
+speculative/contingency picks (LOW).*
