+# Research Summary: sokoban
+
+> Synthesis of `bp/research/stack.md`, `bp/research/architecture.md`, and `bp/research/pitfalls.md`. Single recommendation that all three sub-agents converged on; deviations from the locked grill-phase decisions are zero.
+
+---
+
+## One-Line Recommendation
+
+A **layered TypeScript architecture** вҖ” pure functional reducer for game rules + thin imperative shell for Canvas / input / animation / persistence вҖ” built with **Vite 8 + vanilla helpers** (no state lib, no animation lib, no swipe lib, no storage wrapper), loaded with **`import.meta.glob` eager JSON**, animated by a **30-line rAF linear tween**, persisted with **raw `localStorage` + try/catch**, and tested with **Vitest + happy-dom** (logic) and **Playwright on `vite preview`** (E2E, desktop + mobile).
+
+---
+
+## Convergence Matrix
+
+| Direction | Stack says | Architecture says | Pitfalls says | Verdict |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Level loading | `import.meta.glob` (Vite native) | `import.meta.glob` (eager) | **BLOCKER #12** if you use `fetch` under sub-path вҶ’ adopt glob | **Glob** |
+| State management | Plain `GameModel` + 20-line emitter | Pure reducer + thin shell | Anti-pattern: don't add React/Solid for a single Canvas game | **Reducer + shell** |
+| Animation | Vanilla rAF linear tween (~30 lines) | Snap-then-start tween, rAF loop, no fixed timestep | **BLOCKER #4, #5** if state mutates inside rAF or inputs queue | **rAF + wall-clock lerp** |
+| Touch input | Native Pointer Events + `touch-action: none` | Pointer Events + 24px threshold | **BLOCKER #9** if swipe is attached to `document` / no `touch-action` | **Pointer Events scoped to canvas** |
+| localStorage | Vanilla + try/catch, sync read on boot | Single `storage.ts` owner, namespaced + versioned | **BLOCKER #6, MAJOR #7, #8** for throws / null / schema migration | **Vanilla localStorage** |
+| Game loop | Single rAF, idle-stop, frame-rate independent via `performance.now()` | Wall-clock lerp (not fixed timestep) | вҖ” | **rAF + idle-stop** |
+| Unit test env | `happy-dom` (faster than jsdom); mock `CanvasRenderingContext2D` | Core tests are pure TS вҖ” no DOM needed for logic tests | вҖ” | **happy-dom, scoped via `environmentMatchGlobs`** |
+| E2E target | `vite preview` against `dist/` + desktop + mobile projects | вҖ” | **MAJOR #19** if E2E only runs against dev server | **`vite preview` + Playwright projects** |
+
+All three sub-agents converged on the same stack and architecture with zero conflict. The BLOCKERs flagged in pitfalls are all addressed by the recommended architecture decisions.
+
+---
+
+## Recommended Stack (final selection)
+
+| Component | Choice | Version | Purpose | Confidence |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Language | TypeScript | ^5.6 | All source | HIGH |
+| Build tool | Vite | ^8.1.2 | Dev + build + glob + preview | HIGH |
+| Package manager | npm | (bundled) | Lockfile | HIGH |
+| Level loading | `import.meta.glob` eager JSON | Vite native | Inline 10 levels at build time | HIGH |
+| State | `GameModel` class + ~20-line emitter | 0 deps | Game state + minimal observer | HIGH |
+| Rendering | HTML5 Canvas 2D `fillRect` | native | Flat-vector tiles | HIGH |
+| Animation | Vanilla rAF linear tween (~30 lines) | 0 deps | 100вҖ“150ms NFR-5 | HIGH |
+| Game loop | Single rAF, idle-stop | 0 deps | Battery-friendly | HIGH |
+| Touch | Pointer Events swipe (~25 lines) + `touch-action: none` | 0 deps | Mobile NFR-4 | HIGH |
+| Keyboard | `window.addEventListener('keydown', вҖҰ)` + `event.repeat` guard | 0 deps | FR-1 / FR-3 / FR-4 | HIGH |
+| Persistence | Vanilla `localStorage` + JSON + try/catch | 0 deps | NFR-2 | HIGH |
+| Unit test | Vitest | ^4.1.9 | TS logic tests | HIGH |
+| Unit DOM env | happy-dom | ^20.10.6 | Scoped to DOM-touching tests | HIGH |
+| E2E | @playwright/test | ^1.61.1 | Desktop + mobile over `dist/` | HIGH |
+| E2E server | `vite preview` of `dist/` | Vite native | Tests real artifact (BASE) | HIGH |
+| Commit linter | `@commitlint/cli` + `@commitlint/config-conventional` + `husky` | ^19.x / v9 | Conventional Commits enforcement | HIGH |
+| Deploy | `actions/deploy-pages@v4` | GitHub-provided | Static `dist/` to Pages | HIGH |
+
+**Rejected (with reason):** React/Solid (imperative Canvas, 40вҖ“100 KB), motion / anime.js (16вҖ“50 KB to do `lerp`), Hammer.js (unmaintained since 2016), idb-keyval / localforage (< 1 KB sync data), Zod (10 hand-authored files), fixed-timestep loop (no continuous physics).
+
+---
+
+## Recommended Architecture
+
+- **`core/`** вҖ” pure functions: `reducer(state, intent) вҶ’ { state, anim? }`, `winCheck`, `move`, `history`. Zero DOM/Canvas imports. Fully unit-testable.
+- **`shell/gameShell.ts`** вҖ” only module that knows all subsystems; owns rAF loop; forwards intents вҶ’ reducer вҶ’ animator вҶ’ renderer.
+- **`render/`** вҖ” pure draw: `(state, visualPos, ctx) вҶ’ pixels`. Redraws full canvas every frame (вүӨ30 entities, trivial).
+- **`input/`** вҖ” produces `Intent`. Keyboard (`keydown`, `repeat` guard) + Pointer Events swipe. Buttons go through the same `dispatch`.
+- **`anim/`** вҖ” vanilla rAF tween manager: `start / isBusy / elapsed / snap`. Snap-then-start for interruption.
+- **`storage/`** вҖ” single owner of `localStorage`. Versioned keys (`sokoban:v1:*`). Try/catch вҶ’ graceful degradation.
+- **`ui/`** вҖ” DOM overlays (level picker, HUD, win banner, mobile buttons). CSS handles responsive layout.
+- **`level/`** вҖ” `loader.ts` uses `import.meta.glob`; `validate.ts` enforces schema + invariants (`boxes.length === targets.size`, all positions in bounds, no entity on wall).
+
+### State model (immutable)
+
+```ts
+type GameState = {
+  levelId: string;
+  static: { width, height, walls: Set<Coord>, targets: Set<Coord> };
+  player: Coord;
+  boxes: Coord[];              // order-stable, index = box identity
+  moveCount: number;
+  history: HistoryEntry[];     // entry-based undo stack
+  won: boolean;                // recomputed by winCheck
+};
+
+type HistoryEntry = {
+  player: Coord;               // before move
+  pushedBoxIndex?: number;
+  boxFrom?: Coord;
+  moveCount: number;
+};
+```
+
+### Data flow
+
+`raw event вҶ’ InputPipeline.normalize вҶ’ Intent вҶ’ GameShell.dispatch вҶ’ gameReducer вҶ’ { state, anim? } вҶ’ Animator.start вҶ’ rAF вҶ’ Renderer.draw вҶ’ Canvas`
+
+### Critical algorithms
+
+- **Win check:** `O(B)` вҖ” `boxes.every(b => targets.has(b))` after `boxes.length === targets.size` precheck. Recomputed on move, undo, reset.
+- **Undo:** entry-based O(1) per move, unlimited depth (NFR-6). Walk entries store only `player` + `moveCount`; push entries add `pushedBoxIndex` + `boxFrom`.
+- **Animation interrupt:** snap current tween вҶ’ commit visual вҶ’ start fresh tween from current visual. No input queueing.
+
+---
+
+## Top Risks (BLOCKERs) and How the Recommendation Mitigates Them
+
+| BLOCKER | Mitigation via the recommended approach |
+|---|---|
+| #3 Undo correctness | `HistoryEntry` snapshots player AND pushed box before applying move; reducer overwrites state wholesale on undo. Vitest cases for push/walk/empty-stack/reset-undo. |
+| #4 Undo mid-animation | Logical state commits synchronously at input; tween is render-only interpolation. Undo pops stack + restarts tween from current visual. rAF never mutates logical state. |
+| #5 Animation interrupt | Snap-then-start: cancel in-flight tween, commit visual, start new from snapped position. Single `currentTween` handle. |
+| #6 localStorage throws (Safari private / quota) | `storage.ts` wraps every read/write in try/catch; on failure вҶ’ in-memory fallback, one-time toast, game still playable. |
+| #9 Touch swipe scrolls the page | Pointer Events scoped to canvas + `touch-action: none` + `event.preventDefault()` on `touchmove`. Directional threshold (~24px). |
+| #11 GitHub Pages base path | `base: '/<repo>/'` env-driven in `vite.config.ts`; eager `import.meta.glob` inlines levels (immune to base path). E2E runs against `vite preview` of `dist/` to verify. |
+| #12 JSON level path under sub-path | Eager `import.meta.glob('./levels/level-??.json', { eager: true, query: '?json', import: 'default' })` вҖ” JSON inlined into bundle, no runtime fetch, no path issues. |
+
+Plus **11 MAJOR** risks (deadlock detection, reset/undo interaction, DPR scaling, key-repeat guard, persistence correctness, E2E-vs-build mismatch, CI gating) вҖ” all mitigated by concrete code patterns and test coverage documented in `pitfalls.md`.
+
+---
+
+## Critical Implementation Details (must not skip)
+
+1. **`vite.config.ts` base path:** `base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/sokoban/'` (or `'./'` for user pages).
+2. **Canvas DPR:** `canvas.width = cssW * dpr; canvas.height = cssH * dpr; ctx.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0)` вҖ” and re-apply on resize.
+3. **CSS:** `touch-action: none` on the canvas element.
+4. **Keyboard:** `if (event.repeat) return;` to enforce one-tile-per-press (FR-1).
+5. **Undo correctness:** always recompute `won = winCheck(state)` on undo AND reset, not only on move.
+6. **localStorage namespace:** `sokoban:v1:cleared`, `sokoban:v1:best:<id>`. Versioned for future migration.
+7. **`import.meta.glob` filename pattern:** strict glob `./levels/level-??.json` to avoid picking up stray files.
+8. **Snap-then-start animation:** `animator.snap()` finalizes tween before next reducer call.
+9. **Reset semantics:** clear undo stack on reset (reset = fresh start boundary). Document and test.
+10. **Commit enforcement:** husky v9 + commitlint вҖ” `.husky/commit-msg` shell file; v8вҶ’v9 changed format.
+11. **CI workflow:** `npm ci вҶ’ npm test вҶ’ npm run test:e2e вҶ’ npm run build вҶ’ upload dist/`; deploy job `needs: test`.
+12. **E2E server:** Playwright `webServer: { command: 'npm run preview', port: 4173 }` to test the real built artifact, not dev.
+
+---
+
+## Open Risks / Decisions Deferred to Plan Phase
+
+None blocking. The few **MEDIUM-confidence** items to revisit during planning:
+- Whether to animate undo (snap recommended; tween optional). вҶ’ Architecture treats undo as snap in v1.
+- Whether to add a tiny signal lib for HUD if the picker grows beyond ~5 bound nodes. вҶ’ Architecture allows `nanostores` as future upgrade, not now.
+- Node version pin: Vite 8 requires Node вүҘ 20.19; project requires 20+. Recommend `.nvmrc` with `20.19.0` or `22` and document in README. Fallback: Vite ^7 if older Node 20 patches must be supported.
+
+---
+
+## Confidence Summary
+
+- **Stack**: HIGH on every locked component; HIGH on every rejection rationale.
+- **Architecture**: HIGH on reducer+shell, module boundaries, undo stack shape, eager glob, localStorage wrapper, snap-then-start animation, full-canvas redraw. MEDIUM on undo-as-snap (could be tweened later).
+- **Pitfalls**: 20 risks identified (7 BLOCKER, 11 MAJOR, 2 MINOR); each with concrete mitigation and a confidence label.
+
+All three sub-agents produced output on disk and the recommendation is fully consistent across them. Ready to proceed to **roadmap definition** via `bp continue`.
